name: The Meeting of the Three Kings
description:
Master of the St. Bartholomew Altarpiece (Netherlandish, active about 1475 - 1510)
The Meeting of the Three Kings, with David and Isaiah (recto); The Assumption of the Virgin (verso), before 1480, Oil and gold leaf on panel
62.8 × 71.5 cm (24 3/4 × 28 3/16 in.), 96.PB.16
The J. Paul Getty Museum, Los Angeles
